<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>T 444E Diesel Engine Diagnostics (1997) - SECTION 3.5: CIRCUIT FUNCTION AND DIAGNOSTICS - APS/IVS PEDAL
        POSITION SENSOR/IDLE VALIDATION SWITCH - TESTING APS/IVS CIRCUITS
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="0">
        <title>TESTING APS/IVS CIRCUITS</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If flash codes 131 or 132 are present, perform Testing APS Circuits (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk document="e125_132.xml" xrefid="ef1251805">3.12</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ). If flash codes 133, 134 or 135 are present, perform Testing IVS Switch &#38; Circuits (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk document="e125_131.xml" xrefid="ef1251804">3.11</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ).
            </para>
            <para>These tests systematically check the APS and IVS circuits for:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Short circuits to ground.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Short circuits to unwanted voltage sources.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Open circuits or excessive circuit resistance.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Proper feeds and grounds.</para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>The tests performed on the accelerator pedal assembly check for shorts, opens and correct
                            resistance values, but do not check for proper timing between the two functions. If all of
                            the circuits between the ECM and the accelerator pedal assembly check good (Testing IVS
                            Circuits, Figure
                            <hotlnk document="e125_131.xml" xrefid="ef1251804">3.11</hotlnk>) and APS Circuits (Figure
                            <hotlnk document="e125_132.xml" xrefid="ef1251805">3.12</hotlnk>), then the APS/IVS
                            accelerator switch should be replaced.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step2>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
